class Solution {
    public boolean isPowerOfThree(int n) {
        if (n <= 0) {
            return false;
        }
        while (n % 3 == 0) {
            n = n / 3;
        }
        return n == 1;
    }
}
```

This solution works by repeatedly dividing the input number by 3 as long as it is divisible by 3. If the number becomes 1, it means it is a power of three. If the number becomes any other value, it means it is not a power of three.

This solution has a time complexity of O(log3(n)), which is much faster than the recursive solution.

